extends layout_
block content
    .container-fluid
        section(id="login" ng-controller="visHomeController" ng-init="init()").row.title-row
            .fill-screen.stellar-bg(data-stellar-background-ratio='0.2', style='background-image: url("./images/SCG_main.jpg")')
                .loginPanel.loginPanel-responsive
                    aside.col-sm-6.col-sm-height
                        h4.range-title
                            b Login with
                        .range-list
                            div
                                a.btn.btn-primary(href='/auth/facebook')
                                    span.fa.fa-facebook  Log In with Facebook
                            div
                                a.btn.btn-info(href='/auth/twitter')
                                    span.fa.fa-Twitter  Log In with Twitter
                            div
                                a.btn.btn-danger(href='/auth/google')
                                    span.fa.fa-google-plus  Log In with Google
                    aside.scol-sm-6.col-sm-height
                        h4.range-title
                            b Login
                        .range-list(ng-show="!showForgot")
                            form(action='/login', method='post')
                                .form-group(style='display:inline-block;')
                                    input.form-control(type='text', name='email', placeholder='email address')
                                br
                                .form-group(style='display:inline-block;')
                                    input.form-control(type='password', name='password', placeholder='password')
                            div
                                .formgroup.button.btn.btn-primary(type='submit' style='display:inline-block;') Login
                            a.btn.btn-link(ng-click="showForgot=!showForgot")  Forgot Password?

                        div(ng-show="showForgot")
                            form.forgot-password(action='/forgot', method='post')
                                .form-group(style='display:inline-block;')
                                    input.form-control(type='text', name='email', autofocus placeholder='email address')
                            div
                                .formgroup.button.btn.btn-primary(type='submit' style='display:inline-block;') Reset Password
                            a.btn.btn-link(ng-click="showForgot=!showForgot")  Back to login
                .down-button
                    a.btn(href='#mcgVis')
                        i.fa.fa-arrow-circle-down.fa-4x
        section#mcgVis.row.text-banner
            h1 Visit the MCG
            p
                | Wembley Stadium, Camp Nou, Yankee Stadium and Madison Square Garden are considered among the greatest sporting arenas in the world, but for history, pure drama and emotion, itâ€™s hard to look past the Melbourne Cricket Ground (MCG).
        section.row
            #carousel.carousel.slide(data-ride='carousel')
                // Indicators
                ol.carousel-indicators
                    li.active(data-target='#carousel', data-slide-to='0')
                    li(data-target='#carousel', data-slide-to='1')
                    li(data-target='#carousel', data-slide-to='2')
                // Wrapper for slides
                .carousel-inner(role='listbox')
                    .item.active
                        .carousel-caption
                            h3 CA Grounds
                            p list of grounds in australia
                        img(src='./images/MCG_main.jpg', alt='Scale Mountain')
                    .item
                        .carousel-caption
                            h3 Sydney Cricket ground
                            p Home of Bradman and Trumper
                        img(src='./images/SCG_main.jpg', alt='Mountain')
                    .item
                        .carousel-caption
                            h3 The WACA
                            p Home of pace and bounce
                        img(src='./images/WACA_main.jpg', alt='Rockies')
                    .item
                        .carousel-caption
                            h3 Adelaide Oval
                            p South Australia
                        img(src='./images/Adelaide_main.png', alt='Rockies')
                    .item
                        .carousel-caption
                            h3 The GABBA
                            p Home of AB and some tough cookies
                        img(src='./images/GABBA_main.jpg', alt='Rockies')
                // Controls
                a.left.carousel-control(href='#carousel', role='button', data-slide='prev')
                    span.glyphicon.glyphicon-chevron-left(aria-hidden='true')
                    span.sr-only Previous
                a.right.carousel-control(href='#carousel', role='button', data-slide='next')
                    span.glyphicon.glyphicon-chevron-right(aria-hidden='true')
                    span.sr-only Next
        section#scg.row
            .fill-screen.fixed-attachment(style='background-image: url("./images/SCG_main.jpg")')
        section.activity-section.text-banner.content-filler
            h1 Visit the SCG
            p#nswg
                | Situated in Moore Park in the city's east, the Sydney Cricket Ground is one of the world's most famous cricketing venues. For a stadium in a major centre, it has a relatively limited capacity (a little over 40,000) but this has the direct benefit of ensuring that spectators are close to the action from virtually any point in the ground. Its limited capacity is, in fact, essentially the result of the extension over recent years of seating to most parts of a stadium now devoid of its long famous hill and instead dominated by the Brewongle, Churchill, O'Reilly, Noble and Doug Walters Stands. The green-roofed Ladies pavilion remains, still one of cricket's most famous landmarks.
            .activity-element.col-md-4.wow.fadeInLeft
                img(src='./images/SCG_bradman.jpg')
                h4 Don Bradman
                p
            .activity-element.col-md-4.wow.fadeInDown
                img(src='./images/SCG_trumper.jpg')
                h4 Victor Trumper
                p
            .activity-element.col-md-4.wow.fadeInRight
                img(src='./images/SCG_benaud.jpg')
                h4 Richie Benaud
                p
        section.row
            h2 Nano Gallery
            #nanoGallery3
                a(href='./images/MCG_big.jpg', data-ngthumb='./images/MCG_big.jpg') MCG
                a(href='./images/SCG_main.jpg', data-ngthumb='./images/SCG_main.jpg') SCG
                a(href='./images/WACA_main.jpg', data-ngthumb='./images/WACA_main.jpg') WACA
                a(href='./images/Adelaide_main.png', data-ngthumb='./images/Adelaide_main.png') Oval
                a(href='./images/GABBA_main.jpg', data-ngthumb='./images/GABBA_main.jpg') GABBA
        section#waca.row
            .fill-screen.fixed-attachment(style='background-image: url("./images/WACA_main.jpg")')
        section.text-banner.content-filler
            h1 Welcome to WACA
            p The home of pace, bounce and the Fremantle Doctor
    footer.container-fluid
        h1 Footer